President Joseph R. Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Missouri due to severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from June 24 to July 1, 2021. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Andrew, Audrain, Boone, Buchanan, Caldwell, Callaway, Carroll, Chariton, Clinton, Cooper, Daviess, Grundy, Holt, Howard, Lincoln, Livingston, Moniteau, Montgomery, Ralls, Ray, and Saline are included in the declaration. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding. David Gervino has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and additional damage assessments warrant it. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.